metadata.title: Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche
aws::graph::propositions: Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche has an optional turbonormalized version.
PA-30-200 is an experimental variant of the Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche.
PA-30-200 has two 200 hp Lycoming engines.
PA-30-290 is an experimental variant of the Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche.
PA-30-290 has two 290 hp Lycoming IO-540-G engines.
One PA-30-290 was converted from the PA-30 prototype.
PA-30 Twin Comanche D was the original designation for the PA-39.
PA-39 Twin Comanche C/R is a variant of the PA-30.
PA-39 Twin Comanche C/R has counter-rotating 160 hp Lycoming IO-320-B1A engines.
PA-39 Twin Comanche C/R has modified wing leading edges.
PA-39 Turbo Twin Comanche C/R is a turbocharged version of the PA-39 Twin Comanche C/R.
Piper PA-40 Arapaho was developed from the PA-39.
Piper PA-40 Arapaho is a fully certified version of the PA-39.
Piper PA-40 Arapaho has an entirely different wing from the PA-39.
Piper PA-40 Arapaho has extensive fuselage modifications compared to the PA-39.
Only three prototypes of the Piper PA-40 Arapaho were built.

text:
Optional turbonormalized version.
PA-30-200
Experimental variant with two 200 hp Lycoming engines, one built
PA-30-290
Experimental variant with two 290 hp Lycoming IO-540-G engines, one converted from PA-30 prototype
PA-30 Twin Comanche D
Original designation for the PA-39.
PA-39 Twin Comanche C/R
PA-30 with counter-rotating 160 hp Lycoming IO-320-B1A engines and modified wing leading edges
PA-39 Turbo Twin Comanche C/R
Turbocharged version of the PA-39 Twin Comanche C/R
Piper PA-40 Arapaho
Developed and fully certified version of PA-39 with entirely different wing and extensive fuselage modifications. Three prototypes only.
